Privacy Policy for Piano Shooter

Effective Date: 12th September 2025

Thank you for playing Piano Shooter! Your privacy is important to us. This Privacy Policy explains how we handle your information when you use our game.

1. Information We Do Not Collect

We do not collect or store any personal information such as your name, email, phone number, or address.

We do not track your location.

We do not require you to create an account or log in.

2. Information We May Collect Automatically

Gameplay Data: The game may save your high score, progress, and settings locally on your device so you can continue where you left off.

Device Information: Some non-personal data such as device type, operating system, or crashes may be collected automatically by Google Play Services or third-party services for performance and analytics.

3. Third-Party Services

Our game may use third-party services (such as Google AdMob) to display ads. These services may collect and use certain non-personal information, such as device identifiers or ad interactions, to provide personalized or non-personalized ads.

Please refer to their privacy policies for more details:

Google Play Services

AdMob

4. How We Use Information

To save your game progress (high scores, levels).

To improve game performance and fix issues.

To show ads that help keep the game free to play.

5. Childrenâ€™s Privacy

Our game is designed for a general audience and can be enjoyed by children. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children. If you believe your child has provided personal information, please contact us, and we will remove it.

6. Data Security

All game data (such as scores) is stored locally on your device. We do not transfer or sell any data.

7. Changes to This Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Updates will be posted within the game or on the Google Play Store listing.

8. Contact Us

